be made more amenable </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> sponsorship, delivery or ownership by profit-seeking organisations located within the commercial sector</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There is no evidence that the Coalition Government’s academie</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s and free schools programme have</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> raised standards or n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">arrowed achievement gaps. E</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">vidence from other education systems </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">suggests that in the longer term</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, these programmes will place standards an</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">d educational equity at risk.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The process of academy conversion and free school creation lacks transparency, accountability and excludes </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">important</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> stakeholders from key decision-making processes.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> This lack of transparency raises important concerns about key elements of governance in academies and free schools including the operation of admissions practices, the awarding of contracts and the charging of parents for services and facilities provided </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">by these settings.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Forced academisation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is anti-democratic, contravenes the wishes of parents and other local stakeholders, may result in adverse consequences for children and young people, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">compromises</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the rights of the wor</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">kforce in the schools affected </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">an</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">d undermines public</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> confidence in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">public </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">education system.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The DfE’s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">intended appointment of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">eight</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Commissioners, overseen by small boards of elected headteachers, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to take forward the Coalition Government’s academies and free school programmes at a reg</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ional level, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will exacerbate rather than address problems generated by the absence of an effective intermedi